---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
const title = 'Token Budget';
const subtitle = 'The reader is finite. Slide the graph size; watch the paste break.';
---
<Base title={title} description={subtitle}>
  <article class="etude-page">
    <header class="etude-head">
      <p class="etude-kicker">Etude · Know Thyself, Part II</p>
      <h1 class="etude-title">{title}</h1>
      <p class="etude-relief">{subtitle}</p>
      <nav class="etude-nav">
        <a href="/etudes/know-thyself/">← know thyself etudes</a>
        <span class="etude-nav-sep">·</span>
        <a href="/essays/know-thyself-search/">essay</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <section class="etude-intro">
      <p>A graph that fit cleanly into the model's context at three hundred nodes will fail at three thousand. The corpus didn't get worse. The reader has a bounded window, and once the paste exceeds it, recall and inference both degrade — gradually, then sharply.</p>
      <p>Move the slider. Watch what the model says about Alex's graph as the context fills.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="etude-stage">
      <div class="etude-card">
        <p class="etude-step">Graph size</p>
        <div class="controls">
          <input id="size" type="range" min="100" max="5000" step="50" value="300" aria-label="Graph size" />
          <div class="readout" id="readout">Nodes: 300 | Tokens: ~12,600 | Context fill: 16%</div>
          <div class="presets">
            <button type="button" class="preset" data-target="300">300 nodes (works fine)</button>
            <button type="button" class="preset" data-target="1200">1,200 nodes (friction)</button>
            <button type="button" class="preset" data-target="3000">3,000 nodes (it stops)</button>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="window-wrap">
          <div class="window-bar"><div class="window-fill" id="fill"></div></div>
          <div class="window-warn" id="warn" aria-live="polite"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="chat" id="chat">
          <div class="msg msg-user">here's my graph: <span class="paste" id="paste">[300 nodes pasted]</span> — what's true about Alex?</div>
          <div class="msg msg-bot" id="bot">I see Alex is connected to her sister via a recurring Sunday-call pattern, and her job-search thread links back to a pattern node about deferring decisions when uncertain. Want me to trace either?</div>
        </div>

        <p class="etude-step chart-step">Answer specificity vs context fill</p>
        <div class="chart">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 400 140" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true">
            <line x1="40" y1="110" x2="390" y2="110" stroke="currentColor" stroke-opacity="0.25" />
            <line x1="40" y1="110" x2="40" y2="20" stroke="currentColor" stroke-opacity="0.25" />
            <text x="40" y="128" font-size="9" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.6">0%</text>
            <text x="195" y="128" font-size="9" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.6">50%</text>
            <text x="370" y="128" font-size="9" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.6">100%</text>
            <text x="6" y="28" font-size="9" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.6">high</text>
            <text x="6" y="112" font-size="9" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.6">low</text>
            <path id="curve" d="" fill="none" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="2" />
            <circle id="dot" cx="0" cy="0" r="4" fill="var(--accent)" />
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <footer class="etude-coda">
      <p>The graph is correct. The reader is finite. Retrieval is the bridge. The bound is about the reader, not the corpus — which is why the same shape that matters for Exa over the open web matters for one person's graph at three hundred nodes.</p>
      <p class="fineprint">Long-context degradation is documented across the literature: needle-in-haystack precision drops sharply past mid-window, and recall on multi-hop queries decays well before the model refuses outright. The exact thresholds vary by model; the curve shape doesn't.</p>
    </footer>
  </article>
</Base>

<script is:inline>
  const slider = document.getElementById('size');
  const readout = document.getElementById('readout');
  const fill = document.getElementById('fill');
  const warn = document.getElementById('warn');
  const bot = document.getElementById('bot');
  const paste = document.getElementById('paste');
  const curve = document.getElementById('curve');
  const dot = document.getElementById('dot');

  // Approx 42 tokens/node and 80k-token effective window for the demo.
  const TOK_PER_NODE = 42;
  const WINDOW_TOK = 80000;

  const responses = [
    { max: 0.30, text: "I see Alex is connected to her sister via a recurring Sunday-call pattern, and her job-search thread links back to a pattern node about deferring decisions when uncertain. Want me to trace either?" },
    { max: 0.55, text: "Alex's graph shows a connection between her sister and a Sunday routine, and a separate cluster around job-search uncertainty. The link between those two clusters is faint." },
    { max: 0.75, text: "There's a connection between Alex and a sibling, and another between Alex and a job-related thread. Some uncertainty patterns appear." },
    { max: 0.92, text: "There appears to be some relevant content about Alex in the graph, including family and career nodes." },
    { max: 1.00, text: "I'm unable to process this much context effectively. Please reduce the input size or summarize." }
  ];

  function pickResponse(frac) {
    for (const r of responses) if (frac <= r.max) return r.text;
    return responses[responses.length - 1].text;
  }

  // Specificity curve: ~1 until 0.5, drops via sigmoid past 0.7, floors near 1.
  function specificity(frac) {
    if (frac < 0.5) return 1 - frac * 0.1;
    const k = 14;
    const x0 = 0.78;
    return Math.max(0.05, 1 - 1 / (1 + Math.exp(-k * (frac - x0))) * 0.95);
  }

  function buildCurvePath() {
    const pts = [];
    for (let i = 0; i <= 100; i++) {
      const f = i / 100;
      const x = 40 + f * 350;
      const y = 110 - specificity(f) * 90;
      pts.push((i === 0 ? 'M' : 'L') + x.toFixed(1) + ',' + y.toFixed(1));
    }
    curve.setAttribute('d', pts.join(' '));
  }
  buildCurvePath();

  function fmt(n) { return n.toLocaleString('en-US'); }

  function update(nodes, animateBar) {
    const tokens = Math.round(nodes * TOK_PER_NODE);
    const frac = Math.min(1, tokens / WINDOW_TOK);
    const pct = Math.round(frac * 100);

    readout.textContent = `Nodes: ${fmt(nodes)} | Tokens: ~${fmt(tokens)} | Context fill: ${pct}%`;
    paste.textContent = `[${fmt(nodes)} nodes pasted]`;
    fill.style.width = (frac * 100).toFixed(1) + '%';

    let tier = 'ok';
    if (frac > 0.95) tier = 'red';
    else if (frac > 0.70) tier = 'amber';
    fill.dataset.tier = tier;
    slider.dataset.tier = tier;
    readout.dataset.tier = tier;

    if (tier === 'red') warn.innerHTML = '<span class="warn-icon">⚠</span> inference quality degrading';
    else if (tier === 'amber') warn.innerHTML = '<span class="warn-icon warn-amber">●</span> approaching window limit';
    else warn.textContent = '';

    bot.dataset.tier = tier;
    bot.textContent = pickResponse(frac);

    const cx = 40 + frac * 350;
    const cy = 110 - specificity(frac) * 90;
    dot.setAttribute('cx', cx.toFixed(1));
    dot.setAttribute('cy', cy.toFixed(1));
  }

  slider.addEventListener('input', e => update(parseInt(e.target.value, 10), false));

  document.querySelectorAll('.preset').forEach(btn => {
    btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const target = parseInt(btn.dataset.target, 10);
      const start = parseInt(slider.value, 10);
      const t0 = performance.now();
      const dur = 600;
      function step(now) {
        const k = Math.min(1, (now - t0) / dur);
        const eased = 1 - Math.pow(1 - k, 3);
        const v = Math.round(start + (target - start) * eased);
        slider.value = v;
        update(v, true);
        if (k < 1) requestAnimationFrame(step);
      }
      requestAnimationFrame(step);
    });
  });

  update(parseInt(slider.value, 10), false);
</script>

<style is:global>
  /* === etude page chrome === */
  .etude-page {
    max-width: 38rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .etude-head {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .etude-kicker {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--label-size);
    letter-spacing: var(--label-tracking);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
  }
  .etude-title {
    font-family: var(--serif-display);
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .etude-relief {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }
  .etude-nav {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .etude-nav a { color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; }
  .etude-nav a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .etude-nav-sep { margin: 0 0.5rem; opacity: 0.5; }

  .etude-intro {
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .etude-intro p {
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .etude-stage {
    min-height: 22rem;
  }

  /* === card === */
  .etude-card {
    background: var(--bg-soft);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.5rem 1.25rem;
  }
  .etude-step {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--label-size);
    letter-spacing: var(--label-tracking);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
  }
  .chart-step {
    margin-top: 1.6rem;
  }

  /* === controls / slider === */
  .controls {
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
  }

  /* Apple-style range slider */
  #size {
    appearance: none;
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    width: 100%;
    background: transparent;
    cursor: pointer;
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0.2rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    transition: filter 200ms ease;
  }
  #size:focus { outline: none; }

  /* WebKit track */
  #size::-webkit-slider-runnable-track {
    height: 5px;
    background: var(--line);
    border-radius: 999px;
    transition: background 220ms ease;
  }
  #size[data-tier="amber"]::-webkit-slider-runnable-track { background: rgba(201, 138, 26, 0.35); }
  #size[data-tier="red"]::-webkit-slider-runnable-track { background: rgba(181, 56, 38, 0.35); }

  /* WebKit thumb */
  #size::-webkit-slider-thumb {
    appearance: none;
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    width: 24px;
    height: 24px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    box-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(43, 37, 32, 0.18), 0 0 0 0 rgba(138, 52, 32, 0);
    margin-top: -10px;
    cursor: grab;
    transition: box-shadow 200ms ease, transform 120ms ease, border-color 200ms ease;
  }
  #size:hover::-webkit-slider-thumb { border-color: var(--accent); }
  #size:focus-visible::-webkit-slider-thumb {
    box-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(43, 37, 32, 0.18), 0 0 0 4px rgba(138, 52, 32, 0.18);
    border-color: var(--accent);
  }
  #size:active::-webkit-slider-thumb { cursor: grabbing; transform: scale(1.04); }

  /* Firefox track */
  #size::-moz-range-track {
    height: 5px;
    background: var(--line);
    border-radius: 999px;
    transition: background 220ms ease;
  }
  #size[data-tier="amber"]::-moz-range-track { background: rgba(201, 138, 26, 0.35); }
  #size[data-tier="red"]::-moz-range-track { background: rgba(181, 56, 38, 0.35); }

  /* Firefox thumb */
  #size::-moz-range-thumb {
    width: 22px;
    height: 22px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    box-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(43, 37, 32, 0.18);
    cursor: grab;
    transition: box-shadow 200ms ease, transform 120ms ease, border-color 200ms ease;
  }
  #size:hover::-moz-range-thumb { border-color: var(--accent); }
  #size:focus-visible::-moz-range-thumb {
    box-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(43, 37, 32, 0.18), 0 0 0 4px rgba(138, 52, 32, 0.18);
    border-color: var(--accent);
  }
  #size:active::-moz-range-thumb { cursor: grabbing; transform: scale(1.04); }

  .readout {
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
    font-size: 0.86rem;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.9rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    transition: color 220ms ease;
  }
  .readout[data-tier="amber"] { color: #8a6a2a; }
  .readout[data-tier="red"] { color: var(--accent); }

  .presets {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .preset {
    appearance: none;
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.85rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
    border-radius: 999px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: border-color 180ms ease, background 180ms ease, color 180ms ease, transform 120ms ease;
  }
  .preset:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .preset:active { transform: scale(0.97); }
  .preset:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--accent);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }

  /* === window bar === */
  .window-wrap { margin: 0.2rem 0 1.25rem; }
  .window-bar {
    height: 6px;
    background: var(--line);
    border-radius: 999px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .window-fill {
    height: 100%;
    width: 16%;
    background: var(--text);
    transition: width 280ms cubic-bezier(.2,.8,.2,1), background-color 240ms ease;
    border-radius: 999px;
  }
  .window-fill[data-tier="amber"] { background: #c98a1a; }
  .window-fill[data-tier="red"] { background: var(--accent); }
  .window-warn {
    margin-top: 0.55rem;
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    min-height: 1.1rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }
  .warn-icon { color: var(--accent); font-weight: bold; margin-right: 0.3rem; }
  .warn-icon.warn-amber { color: #c98a1a; }

  /* === chat === */
  .chat {
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0.5rem;
    padding: 0.95rem 1.05rem;
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 10px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    transition: border-color 240ms ease;
  }
  .msg { margin: 0.45rem 0; }
  .msg-user { color: var(--muted); }
  .msg-user .paste {
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    background: var(--bg-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding: 0.05rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .msg-bot {
    color: var(--text);
    transition: opacity 240ms ease, color 240ms ease;
  }
  .msg-bot[data-tier="amber"] { color: #8a6a2a; }
  .msg-bot[data-tier="red"] { color: var(--accent); opacity: 0.92; }

  /* === chart === */
  .chart {
    margin: 0.2rem 0 0;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.2rem;
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }
  .chart svg { width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; color: var(--text); }

  /* === coda === */
  .etude-coda {
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0;
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .etude-coda p {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
  }
  .etude-coda p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .etude-coda .fineprint {
    font-style: normal;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  /* === mobile === */
  @media (max-width: 32rem) {
    .etude-title { font-size: 1.85rem; }
    .etude-card { padding: 1.15rem 1.1rem 1rem; border-radius: 10px; }
    .preset { font-size: 0.78rem; padding: 0.35rem 0.7rem; }
    .readout { font-size: 0.8rem; }
    .chat { padding: 0.85rem 0.9rem; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  }
</style>
